Package CAMs_App.entity

Class Camp

java.lang.Object
CAMs_App.entity.CampInfo
CAMs_App.entity.Camp
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Camp>
public class Camp extends CampInfo implements Comparable<Camp>
The Camp class represents a camp in the system. It extends the CampInfo class, which contains basic camp information. It implements the comparable interface for sorting purpose.

    • Camp

      public Camp(String campName, LocalDate campDate, LocalDate campEndDate, LocalDate regCloseDate, Faculty userGroup, String location, int totalSlots, int campCommitteeSlots, String description, String staffInCharge, Boolean visibility)
      Constructs a Camp object for a new camp using the given camp info.
      Parameters:
      campName - The name of this camp.
      campDate - The starting date of this camp.
      campEndDate - The ending date of this camp.
      regCloseDate - The closing date for registration of this camp.
      userGroup - The Faculty this camp is for.
      location - The location of this camp.
      totalSlots - The total slots for attendees for this camp.
      campCommitteeSlots - The total slots for committee members for this camp.
      description - An introductory description of the camp.
      staffInCharge - The staff that is in charge of this camp.
      visibility - Whether this camp is visible to students or not.
